          <li>
            <a href="http://www.salon.com/2009/09/23/mad_men_oprah/" target="_blank">
              <h5>"Mad Men" minus the racist, sexist parts</h5>
              <p>From Oprah to Banana Republic, pop culture is nostalgic for a dark time. Screw history, bring on the pencil skirts.</p>
              <p><strong>Source:</strong> salon.com</p>
            </a>
          </li><li>
            <a href="http://www.alternet.org/print/story/60278/new_%22mad_men%22_tv_show_uses_the_past_to_reveal_racism_and_sexism_of_today" target="_blank">
              <h5>New "Mad Men" TV show uses the past to reveal racism and sexism of today</h5>
              <p>Just as science fiction often uses a future world to say things about the present you can't say directly, his show uses the overtly sexist and racist atmosphere of a 1960 New York advertising office to talk about issues that persist today but that we are too "polite" to talk about openly.</p>
              <p><strong>Source:</strong> alternet.org</p>
            </a>
          </li><li>
